"Exampl es of hazardous waste sent for recycling include manufacturing solvents, water diluted with biocides, medical plastics, fluorescent lamps, and batteries.",EW_2020.pdf
"We recycled 1,318 metric tons (MT) of non-hazardous waste and 559 MT of hazardous waste from our manufacturing locations in 2020.",EW_2020.pdf
"This represents 40 % recycling rate for our total company waste, which is a 5 % increase from 201 9.",EW_2020.pdf
"Since 2015, Edwards has maintained a consistent total recycling rate of recycling approximatel y 40% of all of our total waste generated, even with continuous fluctuations in our hazardous and nonhazardous waste volumes.",EW_2020.pdf
"In 2020, Edwards invested $46,383 in recycling of nonhazardous waste at our global manufacturing locations.",EW_2020.pdf
"While the cost of recycling varies greatly from country -to-country , Edwards makes every effort to promote recycling regardless of whether there is a financial benefit or a cost.",EW_2020.pdf
"Due to technological complexities in the different countries in which we operate, approximatel y half of our sites pay to recycle, while other half receive payment.",EW_2020.pdf
Other recycling initiatives are required by our landlord and property management companies and incorporated into our lease agreements.,EW_2020.pdf
